    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>English bronze coins minted after 1971 and valued at 2.4 old pennies or one hundredth of an English pound. Prior to 1971, the pre-decimal penny (1d) was a coin worth 1/240 of a pound sterling, its symbol was "d," from the Roman denarius.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
